      "date": "2015-05-07 15:58:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> How big is /tmp on the test nodes, and will that be large enough for the archive? If the VMs have swap, then in theory files in tmpfs can be swapped, but it would be good to have some idea on how large the archive gets during a test run.\n\n/tmp is more than big enough.\n\n \n[root@shadow-22vm5 ~]# df -h\nFilesystem            Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on\n/dev/vda1              20G  1.6G   18G   9% /\ntmpfs                 939M     0  939M   0% /dev/shm\n10.1.0.1:/export/scratch\n                     1008G  424G  534G  45% /scratch\n10.1.0.1:/home       1008G  521G  436G  55% /home\nshadow-22vm4@tcp:/lustre\n                       21G  193M   19G   1% /mnt/lustre",
